  "instruction": "A local handoff page is available at ~/Desktop/webapp_handoff.html and a logo asset is available at ~/Desktop/brand_logo.svg. Open the handoff page in Chrome using the file:// URL and keep it open when you finish. Then build the project described there: create ~/Desktop/webapp/src/, ~/Desktop/webapp/tests/, and ~/Desktop/webapp/assets/; create ~/Desktop/webapp/.gitignore with '*.pyc' and '__pycache__/' on separate lines; create ~/Desktop/webapp/README.md whose first line is '# PulseBoard'; create ~/Desktop/webapp/src/main.py containing the line print('PulseBoard ready'); copy the provided logo to ~/Desktop/webapp/assets/logo.svg; apply the VS Code User Settings from the handoff page; and open the CSS reference URL from the page in another Chrome tab and bookmark it to the bookmarks bar before returning focus to the local handoff page.",
